<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment-Texas,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Correspondent Named in San Antonio</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kelley Shannon, a newswoman in the
Dallas bureau of The Associated Press, has been named correspondent
in San Antonio.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Dallas Chief of Bureau
John Lumpkin.
   Ms. Shannon, 26, succeeds David Sedeno, who recently was promoted
to correspondent in charge of the AP's San Diego bureau.
   Ms. Shannon worked for the Palestine (Texas) Herald-Press and the
Savannah (Ga.) News-Press before joining the AP in Dallas last year.
   She is a native of Austin and a graduate of the University of
Texas.
</TEXT>
