<HEAD>AP Correspondent Named in Wausau, Wisconsin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAUSAU, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert Imrie, a statehouse reporter for The
Associated Press in Bismarck, N.D., has been named correspondent in
Wausau.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Milwaukee Chief of
Bureau Rick Spratling.
   Imrie, 37, joined the AP in Pierre, S.D., in 1985 and transferred
to Bismarck the next year. He previously worked for The Rapid City
(S.D.) Journal.
   Imrie is a native of Bristol, S.D., and a graduate of South
Dakota State University.
