<SECOND>PM-Vietnam-Crash,0129</SECOND>
<HEAD>Twenty Reported Dead as Plane Carrying Soviets Crashes in Vietnam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 20 people were killed when a
Soviet military plane carrying Soviet and Vietnamese officials
crashed in central Vietnam, the Kyodo News Agency said in a report
seen today.
   The Japanese news agency's report from Hanoi quoted ``reliable
sources'' as saying that a 20-member Soviet military delegation and
several Vietnamese officers were killed in the crash Saturday.
   The sources quoted by Kyodo said the plane had taken off either
from Hanoi or from the central coast city of Da Nang.
   Neither the Soviet Embassy in Hanoi nor the Vietnamese government
had reported the incident, the report said.
   The report, filed from Hanoi on Wednesday, included no other
details.
