<FIRST>r i PM-EastGermansDefect     07-13 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-East Germans Defect,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soccer Players Defect While In Sweden</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GOTEBORG, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three East German soccer stars defected
just hours before their team played a Swedish club in an
international cup match, the Swedish team manager said today.
   The leaders of the East German first division club Wismut Aue and
their Swedish hosts Orgryte IF believed the three; one member of the
national team and two from the junior national team left the country
Wednesday.
   ``They are probably already in West Germany,'' Orgryte's manager
Lennart Magnusson said.
   He said the players asked for their passports Wednesday to go
shopping. When they did not show up before the game, their hotel
rooms were searched and found empty.
   ``It's very sad. The East German leaders were in despair and said
they would lose their jobs,'' Magnusson said.
   ``East German teams may never be able to come here again,'' he
added.
   The team left Sweden early today without the missing players.
   Orgryte won the match 2-0.
</TEXT>
