<HEAD>Thunderstorms Strike Arkansas, Oklahoma</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms developing in the warm humid air ahead
of a slow moving cold front extended from eastern Colorado and the
Texas Panhandle across much of Oklahoma and southern Arkansas early
today.
   The thunderstorms produced severe weather in Arkansas and
Oklahoma Wednesday evening. Thunderstorms in Arkansas produced hail
at Midland and strong winds which downed trees around Waldron. Wind
gusts to 58 mph were reported at Dardanelle.
   Thunderstorms in Oklahoma produced golf ball-size hail at Clear
Lake and Howe.
   Showers and thunderstorms also were scattered early today across
northern Mississippi, central and southeastern Alabama, southern
Georgia and South Carolina.
   Elsewhere, showers and thunderstorms developing along a
stationary front were scattered in the upper Ohio Valley and the
mid-Atlantic Coast. Thunderstorms produced up to two inches of rain
in West Virginia, with flooding reported in the Grafton area.
   Showers and thunderstorms also were scattered over the northern
and central Rockies. Thunderstorms in northern Utah produced wind
gusts to 65 mph at the Utah Lake State Park west of Provo.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
in southern New England, eastern Pennsylvania, Florida, eastern West
Virginia, southeastern Kentucky, Alabama, the lower Mississippi
Valley, the Texas Panhandle, northern Colordao, the Nebraska
Panhandle, western South Dakota, Wyoming and Montana.
   Predicted highs: 60s near San Francisco; 70s along the central
and southern California coast, the northern Pacific Coast, western
and central Montana, the Great Lakes and New England; 90s in the
southern Atlantic Coast, the lower Mississippi Valley, the southern
Plains and the southern Rockies; 100s in the desert Southwest; and
80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 54
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 92 at Phoenix and Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 fair; Boston 68 fair; Buffalo 58 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 75 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 72 rain; Cleveland 66
partly cloudy; Detroit 60 partly cloudy; Miami 77 fair; New York 69
cloudy; Philadelphia 70 showers; Pittsburgh 67 drizzle; Portland,
Maine 61 fair; Washington 76 showers.
   _Central: Bismarck 65 partly cloudy; Chicago 68 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 82 partly cloudy; Denver 64 fair; Des Moines 72
fair; Indianapolis 69 cloudy; Kansas City 74 partly cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 71 fair; Nashville 72 fair; New Orleans 77
fair; St. Louis 78 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 76 partly cloudy; Anchorage 62 showers; Las
Vegas 83 fair; Phoenix 92 fair; Salt Lake City 62 cloudy; San Diego
67 fair; San Francisco 56 fair; Seattle 62 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 64 partly cloudy; Toronto 61 partly cloudy.
