<HEAD>Bush Gets Gift of Doll From Hungarian Girl</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bush-Paris Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 8-year-old Hungarian girl's dream of
meeting President Bush came true today at Ferihegy Airport, where
she chatted with the tall, lanky American and gave him a mop-haired
doll.
   With an assist from a local children's TV show and the U.S.
Embassy, Nicoletta Nikolaibisz met Bush on the airport runway just
before he flew to Paris after a two-day visit to Hungary.
   Bush leaned over and listened to Nicoletta talk as he gently
shook her gift of a doll with blue, mop-like hair and a blue dress.
   She expressed her wish to meet Bush when she wrote a letter
asking to appear on ``Three Wishes,'' a popular Hungarian TV show
for children.
   ``The girl said she would like to meet the president, and that
was worked into the (Bush's) official program,'' said U.S. Embassy
press attache Bob McCarthy.
   Nicoletta will appear on the ``Three Wishes'' show in September.
