<FIRST>u i PM-Dollar-Gold     07-13 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Dollar-Gold,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar Slips Lower, Gold Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar drifted lower in quiet trading
today. Gold was slightly lower in sluggish trading.
   In Tokyo, the dollar dropped to 139.05 yen, off 1.45 yen from
Wednesday. Later in London, the dollar traded at 139.28 yen.
   ``I don't expect any major movements in the market until the
release of (U.S.) economic indicators tomorrow,'' said Masato Sanjo,
a dealer in the Tokyo office of Manufacturers' Hanover Trust.
   The British pound sold at $1.6263 compared to $1.6255 late
Wednesday.
   Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday:
   _1.8733 West German marks, down from 1.8755
   _1.6139 Swiss francs, up from 1.6135
   _6.3555 French francs, down from 6.3645
   _2.1111 Dutch guilders, down from 2.1160
   _1,358.00 Italian lire, down from 1,361.50
   _1.1893 Canadian dollars, down from 1.18965
   Gold dropped $3 an ounce in Hong Kong to close at $377.87 on
today.
   Gold opened in London today at $376.85 a troy ounce, compared
with late Wednesday's $379.75. At midmorning, the city's five major
bullion dealers fixed a recommended price of $377.10.
   In Zurich, gold traded for $376.85 an ounce, down from $379.50
late Wednesday.
   Silver bullion was trading at $5.22, down from $5.27 late
Wednesday.
</TEXT>
