<FIRST>r i PM-Soviet-Explosion     07-13 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Soviet-Explosion,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gas Explosion at Soviet Refinery Kills Four, Injures Six</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A propane gas explosion at a refinery in the oil
fields east of Moscow killed four workers, injured six and shattered
windows a half-mile away, Tass reported today.
   The official Soviet news agency said the explosion occurred early
Wednesday at a distillation plant within the Minnibayevsky Gas
Refinery in Almetyevsk, an oil center 500 miles east of the capital.
   A government inquiry determined the explosion was caused by a
propane gas leak, Tass said. All local gas pipelines were shut off
after the accident, and a fire that followed the explosion was
extinguished, it said.
   Last month, a gas pipeline leaked and exploded as two passenger
trains were passing in the Ural Mountains. More than 600 people were
killed.
</TEXT>
