<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Floods     07-13 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Floods,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sichuan Flooding Death Toll Rises to 367</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Severe flooding caused by days of torrential
rainfall in Sichuan province has killed 367 people, the People's
Daily reported Thursday.
   The heaviest casualties were in cities along Jialing River in
eastern Sichuan, the newspaper said.
   Officials say recent rains and flooding have been the most severe
disaster to hit the province _ China's most populous _ in eight
years.
   Heavy flooding also has been reported in coastal Zhejiang and
Fujian provinces, in the southeastern Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region and northeastern Qinghai province.
   Deaths have been reported in Jiangxi province, and other
provinces along the Yangtze River have been warned to prepare for
high water.
</TEXT>
