<HEAD>Mini-Bus Bomb Kills One, Injures Six</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb planted in a mini-bus exploded
in a yard, killing one man and injuring six people, the national
news agency said Thursday.
   The bomb exploded Wednesday night near a major thoroughfare in
the suburb of Mafalala, the news agency said.
   The mini-bus had been parked in the yard since Monday and had
been brought from another country by a friend of the family that
owned the main house, according to Adelia Augusto, wife of the
householder, Humberto Augusto.
   The dead man and five of the injured were living in shacks in the
yard, while the sixth person injured lived in a neighboring house,
the news agency said.
