<FIRST>r i PM-Netherlands-Hostage     07-13 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Netherlands-Hostage,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Holds Woman Hostage in Netherlands, Demands Heroin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HEERLEN, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A German-speaking man wounded a
policeman in a shootout today, took a woman hostage in her home, and
demanded that authorities bring him heroin and his West German
girlfriend, police said.
   The man, whose name was not known, broke into the house of the
52-year-old woman around 2:30 a.m. after exchanging gunfire with
police and slightly injuring one officer, said police spokesman
Herman Naberhuis.
   A radio report said he is West German.
   The kidnapper demanded a supply of heroin and that his West
German girlfriend be allowed to join him, Naberhuis said.
   Police gave him some heroin and his girlfriend was being
interviewed at police headquarters in this southern Dutch city near
the West German border.
   ``I don't know whether she wants to join him at all,'' Naberhuis
said.
   He said the confrontation began when the man broke into a nearby
house known to police for its connections with heroin trafficking,
he said. A woman living there alerted police who were fired on six
times when they arrived.
   The suspect then fled into another house, where he seized his
hostage.
   Heerlen is known for its relatively large population of Dutch and
West German drug abusers.
