<FIRST>r a AM-People-Hirt     07-13 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Hirt,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Trumpeter Al Hirt Honored By Saints Hall Of Fame</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Trumpeter Al Hirt, who played at New Orleans
Saints football games during their early years, was honored by the
Saints Hall of Fame Thursday.
   ``I have Grammies and gold records, but this means more,'' Hirt
said of the Fleur De Lis Award the museum gave him. ``I've been a
fan forever. I love this team.''
   Hirt played at Saints games during the late 1960s, the early
years of the franchise, and said he was their biggest cheerleader.
   ``We used to play right behind the bench and I'd lead the fans in
cheering `Go Saints Go.' Sometimes I'd forget to shut the microphone
off and lead them in something I wasn't supposed to,'' Hirt said.
``Pete Rozelle finally called the team and said `get that guy off
the field.'''
   Hirt, 66, no longer plays at games, but says he still attends.
   ``I never miss a game unless I'm out of town,'' he said. ``This
is the greatest team ever.''
</TEXT>
