<FILEID>AP-NR-07-13-89 2118EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w AM-ArmsControl     07-13 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Arms Control,190</SECOND>
<HEAD>US Negotiator Predicts Soviets Will Agree on Nuclear Defense</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviets eventually will accept an accord on
defense against nuclear weapons if the United States insists,
America's chief Star Wars negotiator said Thursday.
   ``A separate defensive space treaty, in fact, could meet the
stated needs of both sides and could be completed on its own merits,
at its own pace,'' said Henry Cooper.
   ``We have arrived in our discussions with the Soviets over the
past several years at a basic formulation ... for such an
agreement.''
   The Soviets have said the Strategic Defense Initiative, popularly
known as Star Wars, is holding up agreement to limit
intercontinental missiles.
   Cooper, speaking at the Center for Peace and Freedom, said the
Soviets are worried the United States may make important technical
advances and want to be sure it doesn't pull out of a treaty that
prohibits additional defenses.
   ``If we maintain a robust system ... (are) patient in Geneva and
(are) just ... willing to say `nyet' ... the Soviets will eventually
come to join with us in ... a transition to a different strategic
regime in which defenses play an ever-increasing role,'' Cooper said.
</TEXT>
