<FIRST>u f PM-ConAgraPresident     07-13 0298</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-ConAgra President,0311</SECOND>
<HEAD>ConAgra Names Flether President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ConAgra Inc. said today it had elected Philip
B. Fletcher president and chief operating officer of the
multibillion-dollar diversified food interest.
   Fletcher will be the first person to serve in the job alone in
more than 10 years.
   The company has had a five-member Office of the President, which
will continue under Fletcher, said Walt Casey, a company spokesman.
   ``We haven't had a single president and chief operating officer
since probably 1976,'' Casey said.
   The change also means Fletcher, 56, and ConAgra Chairman Charles
M. Harper, 61, will form the executive office of the company in what
Casey described as a strengthening of the management structure.
   ``Our management and board believe it was an appropriate move to
help strengthen ConAgra for continued progress toward our
objectives,'' he said. ``As the companies grow, we'll look for
different ways to strengthen our management structure.''
   Harper said Fletcher was eminently qualified for his new job.
   ``He has 31 years of highly successful experience in the food
industry, including the last eight years in senior management with
ConAgra,'' Harper said.
   Fletcher, who joined ConAgra in 1982 as president of Banquet
Foods Co., has been president and chief operating officer of ConAgra
Prepared Foods Cos. and a member of the Office of the President
since 1987.
   ConAgra's board of directors also added Fletcher and Kenneth W.
Monfort to the company's board, increasing the number of directors
to 12.
   Monfort, 60, retired from ConAgra on May 31 as president and
chief operationg officer of ConAgra Red Meat Cos. and had been a
member of ConAgra's Office of the President.
   ConAgra is a diversified food company headquartered in Omaha that
had sales exceeding $11 billion for the fiscal year that ended May
1989.
</TEXT>
