<HEAD>GM Announces 33 More Saturn Dealers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRING HILL, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors' Saturn Corp. today
announced 33 more dealers to sell its new automobiles beginning in
the fall of 1990.
   About 75 or 80 dealers in 38 large markets are expected by the
time the Saturn cars are introduced next year, officials said.
   ``With the signing of these dealers today, Saturn now has a
strong and geographically diverse base of 59 dealers across the
country,'' said Donald W. Hudler, Saturn vice president of sales.
