   Westinghouse Electric rose 1 to 65\. The company reported
second-quarter earnings of $1.56 a share, up from $1.47 a share in
the comparable period last year.
   Shaw Industries picked up 1 to 16}, also on higher quarterly
profits.
   Sun Electric tumbled 6 to 18|. The company, which had been
soliciting takeover bids, said it had attracted no suitable offers
and expects to remain independent.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $4.31 billion, or 0.13
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks edged
up .16 to 184.31.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose .26 to 376.50, and S&amp;P's
500-stock composite index was up .14 at 329.95.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market gained
1.08 to 447.89. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index closed at 367.64, up .46.
